description: People marched across Europe and beyond at the weekend, denouncing Israel’s genocidal war on Gaza and demanding urgent global action to stop its crimes against the Palestinian people. The demonstrations coincided with the United Nations’ International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People, as the death toll from Israel’s assault on Gaza surpassed 70,000 lives.
title: Mass rallies mark International Day of Solidarity with the Palestinian People

description: TEHRAN – The deputy commander of the Air Defense Force of the Iranian Army says the country’s air defense units are on full alert to counter potential enemy attacks.
title: Air defense network on full alert, says Iranian commander

description: TEHRAN – Rear Admiral Shahram Irani, commander of the Iranian Army Navy, says the Islamic Republic is increasingly viewed as a growing naval power, citing expanded deployments in oceanic waters and heightened participation in international maritime engagements.
title: World now views Iran as a prominent maritime power: Navy chief

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has reiterated that “the only viable and principled solution to the Palestine issue” is to end the organized occupation of historic Palestinian lands, facilitate the return of refugees, and allow Palestinians to exercise their right to self-determination.
title: Only solution to Palestine crisis is ending Israel’s ‘organized occupation’: Pezeshkian

description: TEHRAN – Venezuelan Foreign Minister Yván Gil Pinto has expressed his gratitude to Iran for backing the Latin American nation in the face of US military threats and pressure.
title: Venezuela thanks Tehran for supporting Caracas

description: TEHRAN – Mr. Pope, you too can, like Christ, bring about the greatest miracle of peace of the twenty-first century in reality.
title: A plea for peace in Lebanon

description: TEHRAN – Iran has officially issued land demarcation and ownership documents for the islands of Bu Musa and the Greater and Lesser Tunbs in the Persian Gulf, reaffirming its sovereignty over these territories.
title: Iran officially registers sovereignty over trio Persian Gulf islands

description: TEHRAN – Saudi Arabia’s Deputy Foreign Minister for Political Affairs, Saud bin Mohammed Al-Satti, arrived in Tehran on Sunday for consultations with senior Iranian officials.
title: Saudi deputy FM holds talks in Tehran as Iran calls for stronger regional coordination

description: TEHRAN – Targeting $30 billion in Iran–Turkey trade relations, Tehran and Ankara have pledged to turn their historic and cultural ties into a stronger economic partnership, as President Masoud Pezeshkian and Turkish Foreign Minister Hakan Fidan called for deeper cooperation in trade, transit, and regional security.
title: $30 Billion Roadmap for Tehran–Ankara Ties

description: TEHRAN - Shargh analyzed the escalating conflict between Pakistan and Afghanistan and Iran’s potential role as mediator.
title: Tehran at crossroads of failed mediation

description: TEHRAN - U.S. President Donald Trump is facing a new wave of negative economic polls, indicating that a significant portion of voters are dissatisfied with his administration’s handling of financial and livelihood issues. This growing dissatisfaction, reflected increasingly in public data, could directly impact his political standing, especially ahead of the November 2026 midterm elections.
title: Economic storm ahead for U.S. Congress

description: TEHRAN- The 56th International Film Festival of India- IFFI 2025, concluded Friday in Goa, celebrated a diverse array of cinematic excellence from around the globe.
title: Iran’s "My Daughter’s Hair" shares top honor at Indian festival

description: GOA, India - The Western narrative insists that Russia launched an unprovoked invasion of Ukraine. This story, repeated endlessly by the Atlantic establishment, conveniently deletes the political timeline that made war inevitable.
title: Europe’s war, Ukraine’s ruin, and the case for a new architecture of peace

description: TEHRAN-Iranian director Sarvenaz Nankali staged reading performance of Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen’s “Rosmersholm” at Tehran’s Homa Theater Hall on Sunday.
title: Iranian director stages reading of Ibsen’s “Rosmersholm” in Tehran

description: TEHRAN – Twelve jurors will evaluate films across the International Competition and Eastern Vista sections of the 43rd Fajr International Film Festival (FIFF), which is underway in Shiraz, Fars Province.
title: Renowned global figures serving as jury members of 43rd Fajr International Film Festival

description: TEHRAN - As the “Right to Resist” International People’s Tribunal on Palestine delivered its landmark verdict in Barcelona—finding Israel, the United States, key European states, and other actors guilty of genocide, ecocide, forced starvation, and systematic violations of international law—one of the most compelling expert voices was that of Dr. Omar Nashabeh.
title: Israel waging ‘ecocide’ to erase Gaza’s future, expert warns

description: TEHRAN - India qualified for the  AFC U17 Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2026 after a hard-fought 2-1 win against Iran in their final Qualifiers Group D tie on Sunday.
title: Iran fail to reach 2026 AFC U17 Asian Cup

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Atousa Golshadnezhad defeated China’s Gong Li 4-2 in the final match of the Female Kumite -61kg to win a gold medal at the 2025 World Karate Championships on Sunday.
title: Iran’s Golshadnezhad wins gold at 2025 World Karate Championships

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated Iraq 86-71 at the FIBA Basketball World Cup 2027 Asian Qualifiers at the Nouhad Nawfal Sports Complex in Beirut, Lebanon on Sunday.
title: Iran victorious over Iraq at FIBA World Cup 2027 Asian Qualifiers

description: TEHRAN – Esteghlal football team moved to the top of Iran’s 2025/26 Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) after edging Foolad 1-0 on Sunday.
title: Esteghlal edge Foolad to move top of 2025/26 PGPL

description: TEHRAN – Iranian authorities have lifted export restrictions on handmade backgammon boards, a move officials say will open new international markets, strengthen craft-based employment, and support the country’s traditional artisans.
title: Iran lifts export restrictions on handmade backgammon boards

description: Pope Leo XIV arrived in Lebanon on Sunday, marking the second and final stop of his first foreign tour as head of the Catholic Church, where he is expected to deliver a strong appeal for peace, Al Mayadeen reported.
title: ﻿Pope Leo XIV begins Lebanon visit expected to deliver strong peace appeal

description: TEHRAN – An annual rosewater festival being held in the border city of Baneh, western Iran, has been officially inscribed in the country’s national tourism events calendar, becoming the tenth registered tourism event of Kordestan province, provincial tourism chief announced on Monday.
title: Baneh rosewater festival added to Iran’s national tourism calendar

description: TEHRAN – Venezuela has forcefully rejected recent threats from President Donald Trump to treat its skies as closed, arguing the United States has no legal authority to impose restrictions on another nation’s airspace. Officials in Caracas insist that the move is not only illegitimate but also a direct challenge to the principles of international law.
title: Law above the clouds: Caracas counters Washington’s illegal threats

description: TEHRAN – From hearty stews to fragrant nougat, the flavors of Tabriz offer a vibrant gateway into one of Iran’s richest gastronomic traditions, positioning the historic city as a rising destination for culinary tourism.
title: Tabriz, a heaven for culinary tourism

description: TEHRAN - For 14 years, the remote eco-friendly village of Qaleh Bala has welcomed wildlife enthusiasts to its unique “Journey to the Habitat of the Iranian Ground-Jay” festival — an annual event where residents and visitors come together to honor and protect one of Iran’s rarest native birds.
title: Qaleh Bala, a village where people celebrate endemic Iranian Ground-Jay

description: BEIRUT- Lebanese society has long been marked by debates, disagreements, and deep ideological fault lines. Division is not a uniquely Lebanese pathology but a universal human reflex—dating back, as Rousseau suggested, to the moment the first man staked a claim and declared, “This is mine.”
title: Lebanon’s war anxiety: Between genuine peril and manufactured panic

description: TEHRAN – More than 70,000 Palestinians have been killed as the occupying Israeli regime’s genocidal assault on Gaza continues with no end in sight.
title: Gaza’s death toll hits grim milestone of 70,000

description: Tens of thousands of people have marched in the Philippine capital, Manila, demanding President Ferdinand Marcos Jr’s resignation over a corruption scandal linked to government spending on flood-control infrastructure, Al Jazeera reported Sunday.
title: Philippine protesters rally against trillion‑peso corruption scandal

description: The death toll mounted to over 600 from floods and landslides caused by torrential rains across three countries in Southeast Asia, Reuters reported Sunday, citing regional officials, as relief efforts for tens of thousands of displaced people continued over the weekend.
title: Death toll surpasses 600 in Southeast Asia floods and landslides

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, accused in long-running corruption cases, has submitted a formal pardon request to President Isaac Herzog.
title: Netanyahu seeks pardon as corruption and war crimes cases intensify

description: Four people were killed and 10 wounded in a shooting during a family gathering at a banquet hall in Stockton, California, NPR reported Sunday, citing sheriff's officials.
title: Shooting at California banquet hall leaves four dead, 10 injured

description: The Israeli military launched a large-scale arrest campaign in the occupied West Bank as illegal settlers attacked foreign activists and Palestinians on Sunday, Anadolu reported, citing local sources.
title: Israeli settlers assault foreign activists in West Bank, leaving one critically wounded

description: TEHRAN – The Times Higher Education (THE) Interdisciplinary Science Rankings (ISR) has placed 28 Iranian universities among the top institutions worldwide for interdisciplinary science research, compared to 29 universities in the 2025 rankings.
title: 28 Iranian universities in THE Interdisciplinary Science Rankings 2026

description: TEHRAN – The secretariat of the BRICS Award, Best Cities Experiences and Research, has been established in the country with the aim of sharing experiences, expanding collaborations among cities, and promoting urban diplomacy.
title: BRICS ‘best cities award’ secretariat set up in Iran

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s scientific counselor in East Asia, Australia, and New Zealand, Alireza Pourtavakol, held a meeting with the managers of Universiti Teknologi Malaysia (UTM) to discuss ways to foster scientific and academic cooperation between the two countries.
title: Iranian, Malaysian scientific officials discuss expanding ties

description: TEHRAN – The national week of persons with disabilities is being held from November 29 to December 5 across the country with the theme of “Social Inclusion; Social Integration of Persons with Disabilities”, in line with the International Day of Persons with Disabilities, December 3.
title: Iran marking national week of persons with disabilities

description: TEHRAN- The governor-general of Golestan province, in northeast Iran, expressed hope that holding exhibitions will pave the way for a great leap in the level of economic cooperation between Iran and Turkmenistan.
title: ‘Holding exhibitions hoped to pave way for great leap in Iran-Turkmenistan economic co-op’

description: TEHRAN – A total of 303 domestic and foreign companies are set to participate in the 25th edition of Iran’s International Paint, Resin, Coatings, Composites and Plating Industries Fair (IPCC 2025), according to Iran International Exhibitions Company.
title: Over 300 companies to participate in IPCC 2025

description: TEHRAN – The Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) and the Eurasian Economic Union (EAEU) have reached an agreement to launch electronic data exchange as part of the ongoing implementation of the Iran–EAEU free trade agreement.
title: Iran, Eurasian bloc agree on electronic customs data exchange

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s foreign trade reached 131.054 million tons worth $76.537 billion in the first eight months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21-November 22), according to data from the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA).
title: Iran’s non-oil trade reaches $76.5b in 8 months

description: At least 193 people have been confirmed dead across Sri Lanka as authorities continue to battle rising floodwaters in parts of the capital after a powerful cyclone left a trail of destruction, Al Jazeera reported Sunday.
title: Sri Lanka cyclone leaves nearly 200 dead with hundreds more missing

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Sara Bahmanyar won a bronze medal at the 2025 World Karate Championships on Sunday.
title: Bahmanyar takes bronze at 2025 World Karate Championships

description: The Palestinian death toll in Gaza has climbed past 70,000, according to figures released Saturday by the territory's Health Ministry, which reported 70,100 deaths and nearly 171,000 injuries since the war began in October 2023.
title: Gaza death toll surpasses 70,000 amid Israel's ceasefire violations

description: TEHRAN - Hungary delivered a commanding performance against Iran, beating Team Melli 47-13 at the 2025 World Women's Handball Championship.
title: Hungary crash Iran at 2025 World Women's Handball Championship

description: TEHRAN- In a cherished annual tradition that underscores the strong bilateral ties between Malaysia and Iran, the Embassy of Malaysia hosted a dinner reunion for alumni of the Malaysian Technical Cooperation Program (MTCP) on the evening of September 29th. The event, held at a premier restaurant in Tehran, brought together a diverse group of Iranian professionals who have benefited from the capacity-building initiative.
title: Malaysian embassy in Tehran fosters diplomacy, inspiration at annual MTCP alumni gathering
